arts.ttl: Santiago Gimenez reveals Milan’s last-minute transfer attempt
arts.sum: Feyenoord striker Santiago Gimenez has disclosed an intriguing transfer market revelation. In a recent interview with ESPN, Gimenez shared details about AC Milan’s concrete interest in signing him during the last summer transfer window. The 22-year-old forward explained that Milan made a late attempt to secure his services on the final day of the transfer window. The Italian giants submitted an offer to Feyenoord, but the deal ultimately fell through. Gimenez expressed that joining Milan would have been a dream come true for him, citing his childhood admiration for players like Ronaldo, Ronaldinho, and Kaká.
